@startuml Fittrack_Authenticated_Routing
title Fittrack - Route Scope Flow

skinparam shadowing false

start
:Browser request;
:browser pipeline;
:fetch_current_scope_for_user;

if (route requires login?) then (yes)
  :require_authenticated_user;
  :live_session :require_authenticated_user;
  :Mount LiveView with @current_scope;
  :Call context with current_scope;
  :Run user-scoped query;
else (no)
  if (current-user-aware public LiveView?) then (yes)
    :live_session :current_user;
    :mount_current_scope;
    :Render public content with optional @current_scope;
  else (controller route)
    :Run controller action from :browser pipeline;
  endif
endif
stop

note right
Authenticated app routes:
- /dashboard
- /my-exercises personal CRUD
- /workout-plans, /workouts, /nutrition
- /admin/exercises admin exercise dashboard

Public/current-user-aware library routes:
- /exercises
- /exercises/:slug

Controller media routes:
- /exercise-media/:id safely serves cached media or SVG fallback
- /exercise-template-images/:id serves primary cached/fallback media

Use @current_scope.user in templates.
Do not use @current_user.
end note
@enduml

